Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.10,0:00:20.22,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,Another day of cloudy skies
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.85,0:00:24.73,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,Feelin' low and I don't know why, I
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.35,0:00:28.23,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,Guess it shouldn’t be news to me now
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.67,0:00:32.55,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,It's been this way for centuries but I'm holding out
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.11,0:00:36.24,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,I heard from legends and crystal balls
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.74,0:00:40.36,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,Sun gave warmth to the great and small
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.18,0:00:44.68,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,I saw the smile good old Ray put on their face
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.31,0:00:48.56,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,It ain’t too much to want gentle grace
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.12,0:00:52.44,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,This pessimism brings my brain a schism
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.69,0:00:55.63,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,Splitting up my mind
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.63,0:01:00.38,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,But I know before too soon, I’ll find
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.75,0:01:04.13,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,Footsteps on my porch of ultraviolet kind
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.26,0:01:08.26,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,When the sun comes knocking on my door
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.57,0:01:12.20,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,And after I pick my jaw off the floor
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.58,0:01:16.33,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,I'll say "Come in stranger!"; It's been too long a while
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.70,0:01:20.33,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,He'll hang up his hat with a radiant smile
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.77,0:01:24.27,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,I'll ask where he's been for all of these years
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.59,0:01:28.40,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,We'll talk about his travels over two or three beers
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.65,0:01:33.78,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,I'll hang on every word, looking forward to brighter days
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.40,0:01:37.85,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,When the sun comes back to stay
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.86,0:01:56.05,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,Maybe he just read the sign wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.11,0:01:59.61,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,Or fell asleep waiting on his train
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.17,0:02:04.05,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,And the galaxy express takes a century no less
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.62,0:02:07.99,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,To come back round our way again
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.12,0:02:12.12,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,Every one says you're gone, but I know you're only late
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.62,0:02:16.19,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,I'll leave the lights on if you reciprocate
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.56,0:02:19.94,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,Just promise you're back and we won't get burned
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.06,0:02:23.94,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,You'll be the prodigal sun as far as I'm concerned
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.07,0:02:28.20,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,When the sun comes knocking on my door
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.63,0:02:32.01,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,And after I pick my jaw off the floor
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.57,0:02:36.14,DEFAULT,,0,0,0,,I'll say "Come on in stranger!"; It's been too long a while
